2150, "(fr)Welcome to module TSM-103c, pilot. Don't touch the controls until you are told to do so. You will fail this session if you do not follow instructions carefully."

2151, "(fr)The first function you will learn is targeting. [Press $t$] Target my fighter."

2152, "(fr)In the lower left hand corner of your HUD is your target view.  The top lines display the targeted ship's name and class."

2153, "(fr)The next line shows the distance to your target and its speed."

2154, "(fr)Note the brackets around my ship indicating I am your current target."

2155, "(fr)As I fly out of view, the offscreen indicator will display. It points in the direction you must turn in order to face your target."

2156, "(fr)The indicator moves as I fly around. It is always pointing at your target."

2157, "(fr)Notice how the triangles separate. The farther apart they are, the farther you'll have to turn to face your target."

2158, "(fr)Finally, note the number by the indicator.  This is the distance to your target."

2159, "(fr)The circular gauge near the bottom of your HUD is the radar.  Friendly ships are shown in green.  Hostile ships appear in red. Ships directly in front of you appear in the radar's center."

2160, "(fr)Using your main flight controller turn your ship toward mine.  Stop when my ship is in your center reticle."

