2332, "(fr)For Class A qualification, you learned how to call in a support ship to rearm and repair subsystems. Now we'll show you how to give orders to pilots under your command."

2333, "(fr)Our target for this simulation will be an Argo-class transport."

2334, "(fr)Target the transport. Use your hostile targeting control. [$h$]"

2335, "(fr)Good. Now you'll call in your reinforcements. Press the communications [$c$] key to bring up the messaging window. Select reinforcements [4]. Then select the wing you want to call in. Epsilon wing is your only option, so hit the [1] key."

2336, "(fr)Confirm that you still have the transport targeted. [$h$]"

2337, "(fr)Now have Epsilon wing destroy the transport. Press the communications [$c$] key to bring up your messaging box again."

2338, "(fr)Select [2] to transmit your orders to a specific wing. Then hit [1] to choose Epsilon wing.  By selecting Epsilon wing, you are sending your orders to that wing only."

2339, "(fr)Now press the [1] key, and Epsilon will destroy your target."

2340, "(fr)Well done, pilot! Let's try this again."

2341, "(fr)Order Epsilon wing to destroy Transport 02. Do you remember your previous instruction?  If not, consult the directives list."

2342, "(fr)Good work. Be aware that fighter wings are less effective against larger targets. Bombers or vessels with beam turrets are usually required to destroy warships larger than cruiser class."

2343, "(fr)Also note that reinforcements are not always available, and you will have authorization to issue orders only to specific wings and ships."

2344, "(fr)Now let's order Epsilon wing to depart."

2345, "(fr)Press the communications [$c$] key to bring up the messaging window.  Select [2] for wing, and [1] for Epsilon.  Finally, press [0] for Depart."

2346, "(fr)Excellent work. As you gain experience in combat, using the communications interface will become second nature."

2347, "(fr)All right, pilot. Now it's time to learn about countermeasures."

2348, "(fr)When you launch a countermeasure, you present a new target for pursuing missiles. In theory, the missiles should hit the countermeasure instead of ripping a hole through your hull."

2349, "(fr)You need to use countermeasures to survive in battle, but you'll soon learn this tactic does not always work."

2350, "(fr)For this exercise, we'll bring in a Leviathan-class cruiser."

2351, "(fr)The cruiser will now launch missiles at you.  Press the countermeasures [$x$] key to evade the missiles."

2352, "(fr)Immediately increase your forward velocity to maximum and move away from the pursuing missiles.  Punch your afterburners [$tab$] to gain that extra burst of speed."

2353, "(fr)A yellow triangle will appear on your HUD, indicating the vector of the missile's approach. Try to keep this indicator in the 3 or 9 o'clock position."

2354, "(fr)When the missile is nearly upon you, launch the countermeasure.  Listen to the beeping sound of the missile lock to gauge the distance of the missile. The quicker the beeps, the closer the missile."

2355, "(fr)While launching countermeasures, turn your fighter hard in sharp movements. This will also help throw the missile off your trail."

2356, "(fr)If you evade the missile, an indicator will display in the upper portion of your targeting reticle. This will alert you to the fact that you successfully avoided the projectile."

2357, "(fr)The number of countermeasures remaining is indicated on your HUD below the weapons display. If you run out of countermeasures, call in the support ship to reload."

2358, "(fr)You've sustained heavy damage from those missiles, pilot. You are advised to review TSM-107m. Your chances of survival will be minimal if you cannot use countermeasures effectively."

2359, "(fr)That's enough for evading missiles. Now let's practice firing them."

2360, "(fr)Your Hercules Mark II heavy assault fighter is armed with two banks of Harpoons."

2361, "(fr)Unlike heat-seekers like the Rockeye, you must acquire a lock on your target in order for an aspect seeker to home."

2362, "(fr)However, the aspect seeker is well worth the effort because its homing ability is much stronger."

2363, "(fr)If a heat seeker loses track of its target, chances are it will not reacquire lock. Aspect seekers, on the other hand, will track their targets until they detonate."

2364, "(fr)Transport 03 is now entering.  Let's take this opportunity to learn another targeting control."

2365, "(fr)You have a reticle targeting control [$y$] that will acquire the nearest object inside your reticle. Maneuver your fighter so that my ship is centered on your HUD."

2366, "(fr)Good. Now use the reticle targeting control [$y$] to target my fighter."

2367, "(fr)Well done. Now target Transport 03 using the reticle targeting control. [$y$] Make sure the transport is in the center of your HUD."

2368, "(fr)Excellent. Now let's see how you do with those Harpoons."

2369, "(fr)Notice the red indicator moving towards your target.  That's the Aspect Triangle.  Once it has moved onto your target, you'll see the lock indicator.  This means your Harpoons are locked and ready to fire."

2370, "(fr)Now fire one Harpoon at the freighter."

2371, "(fr)Note how fast the Harpoon moves.  This warhead delivers quite a punch."

2372, "(fr)A round of Harpoons can be fired every 3 seconds.  Fire another round and note the countdown timer in your Weapons Gauge."

2373, "(fr)The Harpoon is almost useless if fired before lock has been acquired. That's a major distinction between the Harpoon and the Rockeye."

2374, "(fr)Now unload your Harpoons until you've destroyed Transport 03."

2375, "(fr)Excellent job.  Let's see how you do against moving targets."

2376, "(fr)In order to gain aspect lock on a moving target, you must keep the target's lock box in a fixed position inside your HUD reticle."

2377, "(fr)We'll now bring in the fighter drones. When the first drone enters, target it and acquire lock. Try to keep the target indicator in the center of your HUD reticle."

2378, "(fr)Once you have acquired lock, fire a Harpoon to destroy the drone.  These drones will not be using countermeasures."

2379, "(fr)Well done.  All aspect seekers function this way, from the Hornet missile to the Helios torpedo. In general, the larger and more powerful the warhead, the longer it will take to acquire lock and countdown between volleys."

2380, "(fr)Now let's have you face a real challenge.  Multiple wings will appear simultaneously.  Destroy them all."

2381, "(fr)You must be in range of your target before you can gain aspect lock.  Hit your burners to intercept the drones."

2382, "(fr)Your missile banks are almost depleted. Call in the support ship to rearm. [Press $Shift-R$]"

2383, "(fr)Well done. This concludes module TSM-107m. Engage your subspace drive to end this simulation."

2384, "(fr)You did not follow instructions. You have failed module TSM-107m. Engage your subspace drive to end this simulation. [$Alt-J$]"

2385, "(fr)Training 5"

2386, "(fr)Welcome to training simulator module TSM-107se, advanced qualification for the Hercules Mark II heavy assault fighter. This module has been designed to acquaint pilots with shield management and the energy transfer system."

2387, "(fr)Congratulations. You have successfully completed TSM-107se, advanced qualification for the Hercules Mark II heavy assault fighter."

2388, "(fr)Your performance was below acceptable standards for TSM-107se, advanced qualification for the Hercules Mark II heavy assault fighter. You will not be authorized to advance until you have completed this unit successfully."

